{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"So I want to talk to you today about AIDS in sub-Saharan Africa."},{"time":4000,"text":"And this is a pretty well-educated audience,"},{"time":6000,"text":"so I imagine you all know something about AIDS."},{"time":9000,"text":"You probably know that roughly 25 million people in Africa"},{"time":11000,"text":"are infected with the virus, that AIDS is a disease of poverty,"},{"time":15000,"text":"and that if we can bring Africa out of poverty, we would decrease AIDS as well."},{"time":19000,"text":"If you know something more, you probably know that Uganda, to date,"},{"time":22000,"text":"is the only country in sub-Saharan Africa"},{"time":24000,"text":"that has had success in combating the epidemic."},{"time":27000,"text":"Using a campaign that encouraged people to abstain, be faithful, and use condoms --"},{"time":31000,"text":"the ABC campaign -- they decreased their prevalence in the 1990s"},{"time":35000,"text":"from about 15 percent to 6 percent over just a few years."},{"time":39000,"text":"If you follow policy, you probably know that a few years ago"},{"time":42000,"text":"the president pledged 15 billion dollars to fight the epidemic over five years,"},{"time":46000,"text":"and a lot of that money is going to go to programs that try to replicate Uganda"},{"time":49000,"text":"and use behavior change to encourage people and decrease the epidemic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55000,"text":"So today I'm going to talk about some things"},{"time":57000,"text":"that you might not know about the epidemic,"},{"time":59000,"text":"and I'm actually also going to challenge"},{"time":61000,"text":"some of these things that you think that you do know."},{"time":63000,"text":"To do that I'm going to talk about my research"},{"time":66000,"text":"as an economist on the epidemic."},{"time":68000,"text":"And I'm not really going to talk much about the economy."},{"time":70000,"text":"I'm not going to tell you about exports and prices."},{"time":73000,"text":"But I'm going to use tools and ideas that are familiar to economists"},{"time":77000,"text":"to think about a problem that's more traditionally"},{"time":79000,"text":"part of public health and epidemiology."},{"time":81000,"text":"And I think in that sense, this fits really nicely with this lateral thinking idea."},{"time":85000,"text":"Here I'm really using the tools of one academic discipline"},{"time":88000,"text":"to think about problems of another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90000,"text":"So we think, first and foremost, AIDS is a policy issue."},{"time":93000,"text":"And probably for most people in this room, that's how you think about it."},{"time":96000,"text":"But this talk is going to be about understanding facts about the epidemic."},{"time":100000,"text":"It's going to be about thinking about how it evolves, and how people respond to it."},{"time":103000,"text":"I think it may seem like I'm ignoring the policy stuff,"},{"time":106000,"text":"which is really the most important,"},{"time":108000,"text":"but I'm hoping that at the end of this talk you will conclude"},{"time":110000,"text":"that we actually cannot develop effective policy"},{"time":112000,"text":"unless we really understand how the epidemic works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115000,"text":"And the first thing that I want to talk about,"},{"time":117000,"text":"the first thing I think we need to understand is:"},{"time":119000,"text":"how do people respond to the epidemic?"},{"time":121000,"text":"So AIDS is a sexually transmitted infection, and it kills you."},{"time":125000,"text":"So this means that in a place with a lot of AIDS,"},{"time":127000,"text":"there's a really significant cost of sex."},{"time":129000,"text":"If you're an uninfected man living in Botswana, where the HIV rate is 30 percent,"},{"time":133000,"text":"if you have one more partner this year -- a long-term partner, girlfriend, mistress --"},{"time":137000,"text":"your chance of dying in 10 years increases by three percentage points."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"That is a huge effect."},{"time":143000,"text":"And so I think that we really feel like then people should have less sex."},{"time":146000,"text":"And in fact among gay men in the US"},{"time":148000,"text":"we did see that kind of change in the 1980s."},{"time":150000,"text":"So if we look in this particularly high-risk sample, they're being asked,"},{"time":154000,"text":"\"Did you have more than one unprotected sexual partner in the last two months?\""},{"time":157000,"text":"Over a period from '84 to '88, that share drops from about 85 percent to 55 percent."},{"time":163000,"text":"It's a huge change in a very short period of time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165000,"text":"We didn't see anything like that in Africa."},{"time":167000,"text":"So we don't have quite as good data, but you can see here"},{"time":170000,"text":"the share of single men having pre-marital sex,"},{"time":172000,"text":"or married men having extra-marital sex,"},{"time":174000,"text":"and how that changes from the early '90s to late '90s,"},{"time":177000,"text":"and late '90s to early 2000s. The epidemic is getting worse."},{"time":180000,"text":"People are learning more things about it."},{"time":182000,"text":"We see almost no change in sexual behavior."},{"time":184000,"text":"These are just tiny decreases -- two percentage points -- not significant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188000,"text":"This seems puzzling. But I'm going to argue that you shouldn't be surprised by this,"},{"time":192000,"text":"and that to understand this you need to think about health"},{"time":195000,"text":"the way than an economist does -- as an investment."},{"time":198000,"text":"So if you're a software engineer and you're trying to think about"},{"time":201000,"text":"whether to add some new functionality to your program,"},{"time":204000,"text":"it's important to think about how much it costs."},{"time":206000,"text":"It's also important to think about what the benefit is."},{"time":208000,"text":"And one part of that benefit is how much longer"},{"time":210000,"text":"you think this program is going to be active."},{"time":212000,"text":"If version 10 is coming out next week,"},{"time":214000,"text":"there's no point in adding more functionality into version nine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217000,"text":"But your health decisions are the same."},{"time":219000,"text":"Every time you have a carrot instead of a cookie,"},{"time":221000,"text":"every time you go to the gym instead of going to the movies,"},{"time":224000,"text":"that's a costly investment in your health."},{"time":226000,"text":"But how much you want to invest is going to depend"},{"time":228000,"text":"on how much longer you expect to live in the future,"},{"time":230000,"text":"even if you don't make those investments."},{"time":232000,"text":"AIDS is the same kind of thing. It's costly to avoid AIDS."},{"time":235000,"text":"People really like to have sex."},{"time":238000,"text":"But, you know, it has a benefit in terms of future longevity."},{"time":244000,"text":"But life expectancy in Africa, even without AIDS, is really, really low:"},{"time":248000,"text":"40 or 50 years in a lot of places."},{"time":251000,"text":"I think it's possible, if we think about that intuition, and think about that fact,"},{"time":255000,"text":"that maybe that explains some of this low behavior change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"But we really need to test that."},{"time":260000,"text":"And a great way to test that is to look across areas in Africa and see:"},{"time":263000,"text":"do people with more life expectancy change their sexual behavior more?"},{"time":267000,"text":"And the way that I'm going to do that is,"},{"time":269000,"text":"I'm going to look across areas with different levels of malaria."},{"time":272000,"text":"So malaria is a disease that kills you."},{"time":275000,"text":"It's a disease that kills a lot of adults in Africa, in addition to a lot of children."},{"time":278000,"text":"And so people who live in areas with a lot of malaria"},{"time":281000,"text":"are going to have lower life expectancy than people who live in areas with limited malaria."},{"time":285000,"text":"So one way to test to see whether we can explain"},{"time":287000,"text":"some of this behavior change by differences in life expectancy"},{"time":290000,"text":"is to look and see is there more behavior change"},{"time":293000,"text":"in areas where there's less malaria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":295000,"text":"So that's what this figure shows you."},{"time":297000,"text":"This shows you -- in areas with low malaria, medium malaria, high malaria --"},{"time":301000,"text":"what happens to the number of sexual partners as you increase HIV prevalence."},{"time":305000,"text":"If you look at the blue line,"},{"time":307000,"text":"the areas with low levels of malaria, you can see in those areas,"},{"time":310000,"text":"actually, the number of sexual partners is decreasing a lot"},{"time":313000,"text":"as HIV prevalence goes up."},{"time":315000,"text":"Areas with medium levels of malaria it decreases some --"},{"time":317000,"text":"it doesn't decrease as much. And areas with high levels of malaria --"},{"time":320000,"text":"actually, it's increasing a little bit, although that's not significant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325000,"text":"This is not just through malaria."},{"time":327000,"text":"Young women who live in areas with high maternal mortality"},{"time":330000,"text":"change their behavior less in response to HIV"},{"time":333000,"text":"than young women who live in areas with low maternal mortality."},{"time":336000,"text":"There's another risk, and they respond less to this existing risk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341000,"text":"So by itself, I think this tells a lot about how people behave."},{"time":344000,"text":"It tells us something about why we see limited behavior change in Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":347000,"text":"But it also tells us something about policy."},{"time":349000,"text":"Even if you only cared about AIDS in Africa,"},{"time":352000,"text":"it might still be a good idea to invest in malaria,"},{"time":355000,"text":"in combating poor indoor air quality,"},{"time":357000,"text":"in improving maternal mortality rates."},{"time":359000,"text":"Because if you improve those things,"},{"time":361000,"text":"then people are going to have an incentive to avoid AIDS on their own."},{"time":365000,"text":"But it also tells us something about one of these facts that we talked about before."},{"time":369000,"text":"Education campaigns, like the one that the president is focusing on in his funding,"},{"time":373000,"text":"may not be enough, at least not alone."},{"time":375000,"text":"If people have no incentive to avoid AIDS on their own,"},{"time":377000,"text":"even if they know everything about the disease,"},{"time":379000,"text":"they still may not change their behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381000,"text":"So the other thing that I think we learn here is that AIDS is not going to fix itself."},{"time":384000,"text":"People aren't changing their behavior enough"},{"time":386000,"text":"to decrease the growth in the epidemic."},{"time":389000,"text":"So we're going to need to think about policy"},{"time":391000,"text":"and what kind of policies might be effective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393000,"text":"And a great way to learn about policy is to look at what worked in the past."},{"time":396000,"text":"The reason that we know that the ABC campaign"},{"time":398000,"text":"was effective in Uganda is we have good data on prevalence over time."},{"time":401000,"text":"In Uganda we see the prevalence went down."},{"time":403000,"text":"We know they had this campaign. That's how we learn about what works."},{"time":406000,"text":"It's not the only place we had any interventions."},{"time":408000,"text":"Other places have tried things, so why don't we look at those places"},{"time":412000,"text":"and see what happened to their prevalence?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":415000,"text":"Unfortunately, there's almost no good data"},{"time":417000,"text":"on HIV prevalence in the general population in Africa until about 2003."},{"time":422000,"text":"So if I asked you, \"Why don't you go and find me"},{"time":424000,"text":"the prevalence in Burkina Faso in 1991?\""},{"time":427000,"text":"You get on Google, you Google, and you find,"},{"time":430000,"text":"actually the only people tested in Burkina Faso in 1991"},{"time":433000,"text":"are STD patients and pregnant women,"},{"time":435000,"text":"which is not a terribly representative group of people."},{"time":437000,"text":"Then if you poked a little more, you looked a little more at what was going on,"},{"time":440000,"text":"you'd find that actually that was a pretty good year,"},{"time":443000,"text":"because in some years the only people tested are IV drug users."},{"time":446000,"text":"But even worse -- some years it's only IV drug users,"},{"time":448000,"text":"some years it's only pregnant women."},{"time":450000,"text":"We have no way to figure out what happened over time."},{"time":452000,"text":"We have no consistent testing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454000,"text":"Now in the last few years, we actually have done some good testing."},{"time":459000,"text":"In Kenya, in Zambia, and a bunch of countries,"},{"time":462000,"text":"there's been testing in random samples of the population."},{"time":465000,"text":"But this leaves us with a big gap in our knowledge."},{"time":468000,"text":"So I can tell you what the prevalence was in Kenya in 2003,"},{"time":471000,"text":"but I can't tell you anything about 1993 or 1983."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474000,"text":"So this is a problem for policy. It was a problem for my research."},{"time":478000,"text":"And I started thinking about how else might we figure out"},{"time":482000,"text":"what the prevalence of HIV was in Africa in the past."},{"time":484000,"text":"And I think that the answer is, we can look at mortality data,"},{"time":488000,"text":"and we can use mortality data to figure out what the prevalence was in the past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492000,"text":"To do this, we're going to have to rely on the fact"},{"time":494000,"text":"that AIDS is a very specific kind of disease."},{"time":496000,"text":"It kills people in the prime of their lives."},{"time":498000,"text":"Not a lot of other diseases have that profile. And you can see here --"},{"time":501000,"text":"this is a graph of death rates by age in Botswana and Egypt."},{"time":505000,"text":"Botswana is a place with a lot of AIDS,"},{"time":507000,"text":"Egypt is a place without a lot of AIDS."},{"time":509000,"text":"And you see they have pretty similar death rates among young kids and old people."},{"time":512000,"text":"That suggests it's pretty similar levels of development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515000,"text":"But in this middle region, between 20 and 45,"},{"time":518000,"text":"the death rates in Botswana are much, much, much higher than in Egypt."},{"time":522000,"text":"But since there are very few other diseases that kill people,"},{"time":526000,"text":"we can really attribute that mortality to HIV."},{"time":529000,"text":"But because people who died this year of AIDS got it a few years ago,"},{"time":533000,"text":"we can use this data on mortality to figure out what HIV prevalence was in the past."},{"time":538000,"text":"So it turns out, if you use this technique,"},{"time":540000,"text":"actually your estimates of prevalence are very close"},{"time":542000,"text":"to what we get from testing random samples in the population,"},{"time":545000,"text":"but they're very, very different than what UNAIDS tells us the prevalences are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550000,"text":"So this is a graph of prevalence estimated by UNAIDS,"},{"time":553000,"text":"and prevalence based on the mortality data"},{"time":555000,"text":"for the years in the late 1990s in nine countries in Africa."},{"time":559000,"text":"You can see, almost without exception,"},{"time":561000,"text":"the UNAIDS estimates are much higher than the mortality-based estimates."},{"time":565000,"text":"UNAIDS tell us that the HIV rate in Zambia is 20 percent,"},{"time":569000,"text":"and mortality estimates suggest it's only about 5 percent."},{"time":573000,"text":"And these are not trivial differences in mortality rates."},{"time":576000,"text":"So this is another way to see this."},{"time":578000,"text":"You can see that for the prevalence to be as high as UNAIDS says,"},{"time":580000,"text":"we have to really see 60 deaths per 10,000"},{"time":582000,"text":"rather than 20 deaths per 10,000 in this age group."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586000,"text":"I'm going to talk a little bit in a minute"},{"time":588000,"text":"about how we can use this kind of information to learn something"},{"time":591000,"text":"that's going to help us think about the world."},{"time":593000,"text":"But this also tells us that one of these facts"},{"time":595000,"text":"that I mentioned in the beginning may not be quite right."},{"time":598000,"text":"If you think that 25 million people are infected,"},{"time":600000,"text":"if you think that the UNAIDS numbers are much too high,"},{"time":603000,"text":"maybe that's more like 10 or 15 million."},{"time":605000,"text":"It doesn't mean that AIDS isn't a problem. It's a gigantic problem."},{"time":609000,"text":"But it does suggest that that number might be a little big."},{"time":613000,"text":"What I really want to do, is I want to use this new data"},{"time":615000,"text":"to try to figure out what makes the HIV epidemic grow faster or slower."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619000,"text":"And I said in the beginning, I wasn't going to tell you about exports."},{"time":622000,"text":"When I started working on these projects,"},{"time":624000,"text":"I was not thinking at all about economics,"},{"time":626000,"text":"but eventually it kind of sucks you back in."},{"time":629000,"text":"So I am going to talk about exports and prices."},{"time":632000,"text":"And I want to talk about the relationship between economic activity,"},{"time":635000,"text":"in particular export volume, and HIV infections."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639000,"text":"So obviously, as an economist, I'm deeply familiar"},{"time":643000,"text":"with the fact that development, that openness to trade,"},{"time":645000,"text":"is really good for developing countries."},{"time":647000,"text":"It's good for improving people's lives."},{"time":650000,"text":"But openness and inter-connectedness, it comes with a cost"},{"time":652000,"text":"when we think about disease. I don't think this should be a surprise."},{"time":655000,"text":"On Wednesday, I learned from Laurie Garrett"},{"time":657000,"text":"that I'm definitely going to get the bird flu,"},{"time":659000,"text":"and I wouldn't be at all worried about that"},{"time":662000,"text":"if we never had any contact with Asia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665000,"text":"And HIV is actually particularly closely linked to transit."},{"time":669000,"text":"The epidemic was introduced to the US"},{"time":671000,"text":"by actually one male steward on an airline flight,"},{"time":675000,"text":"who got the disease in Africa and brought it back."},{"time":677000,"text":"And that was the genesis of the entire epidemic in the US."},{"time":680000,"text":"In Africa, epidemiologists have noted for a long time"},{"time":684000,"text":"that truck drivers and migrants are more likely to be infected than other people."},{"time":688000,"text":"Areas with a lot of economic activity --"},{"time":690000,"text":"with a lot of roads, with a lot of urbanization --"},{"time":693000,"text":"those areas have higher prevalence than others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695000,"text":"But that actually doesn't mean at all"},{"time":697000,"text":"that if we gave people more exports, more trade, that that would increase prevalence."},{"time":701000,"text":"By using this new data, using this information about prevalence over time,"},{"time":705000,"text":"we can actually test that. And so it seems to be --"},{"time":709000,"text":"fortunately, I think -- it seems to be the case"},{"time":711000,"text":"that these things are positively related."},{"time":713000,"text":"More exports means more AIDS. And that effect is really big."},{"time":717000,"text":"So the data that I have suggests that if you double export volume,"},{"time":721000,"text":"it will lead to a quadrupling of new HIV infections."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726000,"text":"So this has important implications both for forecasting and for policy."},{"time":729000,"text":"From a forecasting perspective, if we know where trade is likely to change,"},{"time":733000,"text":"for example, because of the African Growth and Opportunities Act"},{"time":736000,"text":"or other policies that encourage trade,"},{"time":738000,"text":"we can actually think about which areas are likely to be heavily infected with HIV."},{"time":743000,"text":"And we can go and we can try to have pre-emptive preventive measures there."},{"time":749000,"text":"Likewise, as we're developing policies to try to encourage exports,"},{"time":752000,"text":"if we know there's this externality --"},{"time":754000,"text":"this extra thing that's going to happen as we increase exports --"},{"time":756000,"text":"we can think about what the right kinds of policies are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":759000,"text":"But it also tells us something about one of these things that we think that we know."},{"time":762000,"text":"Even though it is the case that poverty is linked to AIDS,"},{"time":765000,"text":"in the sense that Africa is poor and they have a lot of AIDS,"},{"time":768000,"text":"it's not necessarily the case that improving poverty -- at least in the short run,"},{"time":772000,"text":"that improving exports and improving development --"},{"time":774000,"text":"it's not necessarily the case that that's going to lead"},{"time":776000,"text":"to a decline in HIV prevalence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":779000,"text":"So throughout this talk I've mentioned a few times"},{"time":781000,"text":"the special case of Uganda, and the fact that"},{"time":783000,"text":"it's the only country in sub-Saharan Africa with successful prevention."},{"time":787000,"text":"It's been widely heralded."},{"time":789000,"text":"It's been replicated in Kenya, and Tanzania, and South Africa and many other places."},{"time":795000,"text":"But now I want to actually also question that."},{"time":799000,"text":"Because it is true that there was a decline in prevalence"},{"time":802000,"text":"in Uganda in the 1990s. It's true that they had an education campaign."},{"time":806000,"text":"But there was actually something else that happened in Uganda in this period."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812000,"text":"There was a big decline in coffee prices."},{"time":814000,"text":"Coffee is Uganda's major export."},{"time":816000,"text":"Their exports went down a lot in the early 1990s -- and actually that decline lines up"},{"time":821000,"text":"really, really closely with this decline in new HIV infections."},{"time":825000,"text":"So you can see that both of these series --"},{"time":828000,"text":"the black line is export value, the red line is new HIV infections --"},{"time":831000,"text":"you can see they're both increasing."},{"time":833000,"text":"Starting about 1987 they're both going down a lot."},{"time":835000,"text":"And then actually they track each other"},{"time":837000,"text":"a little bit on the increase later in the decade."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839000,"text":"So if you combine the intuition in this figure"},{"time":841000,"text":"with some of the data that I talked about before,"},{"time":844000,"text":"it suggests that somewhere between 25 percent and 50 percent"},{"time":848000,"text":"of the decline in prevalence in Uganda"},{"time":850000,"text":"actually would have happened even without any education campaign."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854000,"text":"But that's enormously important for policy."},{"time":856000,"text":"We're spending so much money to try to replicate this campaign."},{"time":858000,"text":"And if it was only 50 percent as effective as we think that it was,"},{"time":861000,"text":"then there are all sorts of other things"},{"time":863000,"text":"maybe we should be spending our money on instead."},{"time":865000,"text":"Trying to change transmission rates by treating other sexually transmitted diseases."},{"time":869000,"text":"Trying to change them by engaging in male circumcision."},{"time":871000,"text":"There are tons of other things that we should think about doing."},{"time":873000,"text":"And maybe this tells us that we should be thinking more about those things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":877000,"text":"I hope that in the last 16 minutes I've told you something that you didn't know about AIDS,"},{"time":882000,"text":"and I hope that I've gotten you questioning a little bit"},{"time":884000,"text":"some of the things that you did know."},{"time":886000,"text":"And I hope that I've convinced you maybe"},{"time":888000,"text":"that it's important to understand things about the epidemic"},{"time":890000,"text":"in order to think about policy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":893000,"text":"But more than anything, you know, I'm an academic."},{"time":895000,"text":"And when I leave here, I'm going to go back"},{"time":897000,"text":"and sit in my tiny office, and my computer, and my data."},{"time":900000,"text":"And the thing that's most exciting about that"},{"time":902000,"text":"is every time I think about research, there are more questions."},{"time":905000,"text":"There are more things that I think that I want to do."},{"time":907000,"text":"And what's really, really great about being here"},{"time":909000,"text":"is I'm sure that the questions that you guys have"},{"time":911000,"text":"are very, very different than the questions that I think up myself."},{"time":914000,"text":"And I can't wait to hear about what they are."},{"time":916000,"text":"So thank you very much."}]}]}